5 Stars Out Of 5



A very good contribution to a very good series


September 15, 2012



RICHARD HOLT
Clovis, NM



Age: 45-54
Gender: male
  

Quality:




5
 
Value:




4
 
Meets Expectations:




5
  
            The Pillar New Testament Commentary is written with the understanding that God stands over us; "we do not stand in judgment of him." This perspective protects against some of the more speculative and skeptical approaches to Bible study. Edwards's approach is definitely in harmony with the aim of the series. The style of writing is both informative and interesting. Many commentaries attempt to meet the needs of scholars and lay persons. Edwards actually succeeds in doing so. The introduction is also very well written. I highly recommend it.
        














Was this review helpful?
